  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "6OqIaypog9q38aygvakvtUfDNw8=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "When Powerhouse generates code for a document model (either automatically via Vetra or manually via `ph generate`), it creates two key directories:\n\n- **`gen/`** - Auto-generated code that must NOT be manually edited. It will be overwritten on regeneration. Contains:\n  - `types.ts` - TypeScript interfaces from GraphQL schema (state types, input types)\n  - `creators.ts` - Action creator functions (e.g., `addTodoItem({ text: '...' })`)\n  - `utils.ts` - Utility functions including `createDocument()`\n  - `reducer.ts` - Reducer interface definition\n  - Module-specific operation types\n\n- **`src/`** - Your custom implementation. Contains:\n  - `reducers/` - Skeleton reducer files with function stubs for each operation\n  - `tests/` - Test file scaffolding\n\nThis separation ensures generated code stays in sync with specifications while preserving your custom business logic.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z"
    }
  },
